Code:

def find_repeating_char(string):
    empty_list=[]
    for i in range(len(string)):
        if string[i] not in empty_list:
            empty_list+=string[i]
            if len(empty_list)==len(string):
                print("1")
                break
        else:
            print(f"{string[i]} is repeated.")
            break
        
name=input("Enter your name:")
find_repeating_char(name)

Output:

Case 1:

Enter your name:veeralakshmi
e is repeated.

Case 2:

Enter your name:VEJMCP
1
